Docking benchmark results

metrics <- readxl::read_excel("DUD-E_results.xlsx", "Table_results", skip=1)
metrics <- metrics[metrics$Program != "rDock_preHTVS",]
metrics <- metrics[grep("_norm", metrics$Program, invert=T),]
# metrics[intersect(grep("Vina", metrics$Program),
                  # grep("dev3", metrics$Program, invert = T)), ]$Program <- "Vina_1.2.1_AD4"


metrics[metrics$System == "MMP13" & metrics$Program == "Vina_1.2.1_AD4", ]$time <- "190:39:19"
metrics[metrics$System == "MMP13" & metrics$Program == "Vina_1.2.1_AD4_norm", ]$time <- "190:39:19"
metrics <- metrics %>%
  mutate(`timelig` = as.numeric(gsub("s", "", lubridate::as.duration(lubridate::hms(time))/Ligands)))

colnums <- grep("AUC", colnames(metrics)):length(colnames(metrics))
metrics[, colnums] <- sapply(metrics[,colnums], as.numeric)

1 Enrichment factors

Figure 1.1: Heatmaps of normalized Enrichment Factors at different %s for the different programs and systems. Rows (systems) are sliced by type of system, according to the left annotation. Columns (programs) are sorted by decreasing value of average EF across all systems for each %. The program that yields the best value for each system in each case is highlighted with a point. Normalization of EFs is performed by dividing each EF value by the best possible value that can be obtained for the corresponding % (which depends on the library size and amount of actives in it) and then applying a log10 transformation (0,001 is added to all values to avoid zeroes).

2 AUC and time per ligand

Figure 2.1: Heatmaps of AUC values and time per ligand (time divided by total ligands). As before, rows (systems) are sliced by type of system, according to the left annotation and columns (programs) are sorted by decreasing (or increasing, respectively) value of the average of the metric across all systems. The program that yields the best value for each system in each case is highlighted with a point. Upper legend corresponds to AUC heatmap and the bottom one to time per ligand.
